      "notes": [
        "Treat these values as a blocking pass for rig setup, not as final approved animation.",
        "The real production walk should be authored manually in Rive after the segmented SVG parts are rigged.",
        "Rig uses explicit upper+lower segments on arms and legs plus ankle, toe, pelvis, chest, and neck controls — see rig_requirements.",
        "Passing pose sample is frame 18 and 53, contact is frame 0 and 35, and loop returns at frame 70.",
        "Arms and legs remain mirrored with a 35-frame offset between sides.",
        "Eyelids blink independently every ~4s, not part of walk cycle keyframes."
      ],
      "rig_requirements": [
        "root bone: Y-translate only (bodyBob). Origin at feet center.",
        "pelvis_group: pivot at 50% x, 66% y of fill box.",
        "chest_group: pivot at 50% x, 35% y of fill box.",
        "neck_group: pivot at 50% x, 88% y of fill box.",
        "arm_upper_left + arm_upper_right: pivot at shoulder top.",
        "arm_lower_left + arm_lower_right: pivot at elbow top.",
        "leg_upper_left + leg_upper_right: pivot at hip top.",
        "leg_lower_left + leg_lower_right: pivot at knee top.",
        "foot_left + foot_right: pivot at ankle (24% x, 32% y of foot bounds).",
        "toe_left + toe_right: pivot at 8% x, 56% y of foot-tip bounds.",
        "head_group: pivot at neck center.",
        "hat: pivot at brim bottom-center.",
        "cape/backpack: use top-anchored lagging secondary motion.",
        "backpack: pivot at strap-top center.",
        "shadow: scaleX only, no pivot needed."
      ],
